timeline.bodyText:
I think these two can be combined. We can just have Option.of(T value) if the value is null we know it represents empty. Do we have any added benefit of having two separate methods? With these two methods - the user will either always use ofNullable just to be safe or will have to write something like
Option<T> patchValue;
if( value != null) { 
      patchValue = Option.of(value); 
} else { 
     patchValue = Option.empty();
}

